# RAG Pipeline & Workers

## Worker Boundary

- PDF parsing: `@src/workers/pdfWorker.ts`
- Embeddings: `@src/workers/embeddingWorker.ts`
- Main thread orchestrates via `@src/lib/rag/ragService.ts` — no blocking loops in UI code.

<example>
// Main thread: postMessage to worker, await typed response
worker.postMessage({ type: 'embed', chunks });
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// Main thread: run transformers model synchronously in component
const embeddings = await pipeline('embed', text);
</example>

## OPFS Vectors

- Store float32 embedding blobs in OPFS via `@src/lib/opfs.ts`.
- Keep IndexedDB `documentChunks` for metadata and embeddingId references only.
- Close/release handles after writes to avoid OPFS leaks.

## Chunking

- Token-aware chunking in `@src/lib/rag/chunking.ts`; reuse constants, do not duplicate magic numbers.
- Message types defined in `@src/lib/rag/types.ts` — extend there for new worker payloads.

## Performance

- Batch embedding requests where possible.
- Propagate worker errors to UI with actionable messages; log worker `error` events without document content.

## Testing

- Unit-test chunking and ragService with mocked workers/OPFS.
- See `@src/lib/rag/chunking.test.ts`, `@src/lib/rag/ragService.test.ts`, `@src/lib/opfs.test.ts`.
